snippet.textDisplay:
Section B
Q#2

Connections in data communication are methods to link devices for data exchange. They include Point-to-Point (direct link between two devices) and Multipoint (shared link for multiple devices). Connections can be Wired (cables like Ethernet or fiber optics) or Wireless (Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, etc.). Data flow modes include Half-Duplex (one direction at a time) and Full-Duplex (simultaneous bidirectional flow). Serial connections transmit data bit by bit, while Parallel sends multiple bits simultaneously. The choice of connection depends on speed, distance, cost, and application needs.
